column5: My Boss had this made last spring ,its got 2 200 HO E TECS on it ,runs high 60s we had about 4 tonnes in it last summer a few times no effort at all,burns a bit of fuel thou lol ,im trying to convince him to put 4 riggers across the back,shes 26ft with a 10 ft beam
Now that looks like a mean solid machine bring on the waves.
worst part is I gotta ride in it all week then get in my 17ft
That is one mean work barge!!!  By the way...What the hell would you catch trolling in the mid 60's???LOL
That boat would handle some serious water thats for sure !!!!!,and shes well powered too ,nice rig:thumbsup_anim:
Dude,I could troll out of that thing
HMMM now it does have a trailer if we where to drag it your way a day on the water for skis maybe
You could have a casting deck that would hold 4 people on there
ahhhh yes sad part is I dont think shes carried a fishing rod yet ,hopefully this season
